						               													<description>Two of the &amp;quot;Test Series&amp;quot; games released by Poultron Press, the forerunner of SPI. Flying Fortress was Test Series Game 2 and Flying Fortress II was Test Series Game 10. The games covered the Allied strategic bombing in Europe during World War II.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The games covered both US and British bombing efforts. Planes include B-17s, B-24s, Lancasters, and Halifaxes. (B-29s are in the optional rules.)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The games were reportedly the first to use hidden victory conditions (the &amp;quot;nidden victory points&amp;quot; mechanism is the closest available equivalent). Flying Fortress II may have been the first game with double-sided counters (the back used for step reduction).&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each turn in the game was a separate &amp;quot;tactical mission&amp;quot; game representing a month of real time. These turns were linked together to make a campaign. The mission game rules were divided into basic, standard, and advanced levels.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
